category.Name: category
category.Description:
To find all OASIS assessments, set to “OASIS”. To find more specific OASIS assessments to following values can be used:

  • OASIS-SOC
  • OASIS-ROC
  • OASIS-RECERTIFICATION
  • OASIS-OTHER-FOLLOWUP
  • OASIS-TRANSFER-NO-DISCHARGE
  • OASIS-TRANSFER-DISCHARGE
  • OASIS-DEATH
  • OASIS-DISCHARGE

patient.Name: patient
patient.Optional: Either the patient or subject parameter must be provided.

period.Name: period
period.Description: The date of service being documented.

subject.Name: subject
subject.Optional: Either the patient or subject parameter must be provided.

Bundle.Name: Bundle
Bundle.Description: Resource bundle. For more information, refer to the FHIR specification.

DocumentReference.Name: DocumentReference
DocumentReference.Description: An instance of the R4 DocumentReference resource.

authenticator.Name: authenticator
authenticator.Description: What organization is associated with the assessment.

attachment.Name: attachment
attachment.Description: Reference to the binary documenting containing the assessment data.

encounter.Name: encounter
encounter.Description: Reference to the encounter where the assessment was documented.

period.Name: period
period.Description: The date the assessment was completed.

description.Name: description
description.Description: A string in the format <reason for assessment> OASIS Assessment for <Patient>.

docStatus.Name: docStatus
docStatus.Description:
One of the following docstatus values:
<ul><li>preliminary
<li>final
<li>amended

identifier.Name: identifier
identifier.Description: The assessment identifier from the Epic system

subject.Name: subject
subject.Description: The patient who is the subject of the note.
